@
Reasons for supporting many platforms


Bugs in any part of the tree can be revealed
on different processors:

race conditions
word alignment issues
byte ordering issues
over-/underflows and pointer size mismatches
bit operation issues, especially on signed integers
hardware emulation issues (e.g. in softfloat code)
default signedness of "char" type




